In [[category theory]], a '''finitely generated object''' is the quotient of a [[free object]] over a [[finite set]], in the sense that it is the target of a [[epimorphism|regular epimorphism]] from a free object that is free on a finite set.<ref>{{nlab|id=finitely+generated+object|title=finitely generated object}}.</ref>
For instance, one way of defining a [[finitely generated group]] is that it is the image of a [[group homomorphism]] from a finitely generated [[free group]].
