{{about|the psychological condition||Stir crazy (disambiguation)}}
'''Stir crazy''' is an experience of anxiety about being trapped in a future of boredom; it associated with prisoners and adolescents.<ref name=EncycPhob>{{cite book|last1=Adamec|first1=Christine|title=The Encyclopedia of Phobias, Fears, and Anxieties, Third Edition|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=E2imSyZZDh0C|publisher=Infobase Publishing|year=2010|isbn=9781438120980|page=135}}</ref>  It is also called "chronophobia".<ref name=EncycPhob/>  According to the [[Oxford English Dictionary]] the phrase dates back to 1908 and stems from the slang term "stir" for prison.<ref>"Stir, ''n''.<sup>3</sup>" [[Oxford English Dictionary]] online, accessed June 30, 2007.</ref> 

